# Token Discipline

## Reading

- NEVER read `node_modules/`, `package-lock.json`, or `frontend/assets/`
- NEVER read `frontend/admin/index.html` or `frontend/index.html` top-to-bottom.
  Grep for the function/id first, then read only the surrounding ~80 lines
- Trust the project-context rule for architecture; do not re-explore the repo
  unless the task names a file that the map does not cover
- Read a file at most once per task; work from what you read

## Editing

- Smallest diff that completes the task. No drive-by refactors, renames,
  or formatting churn outside the named files
- Do not regenerate whole files when a targeted edit works
- No new dependencies unless the task explicitly says to install one

## Chat hygiene

- One roadmap day = one chat. Do not continue into the next day in the same chat
- If a task is done, stop. Suggest follow-ups in one line, do not start them
- Verification = one curl or one browser check, stated in one line
